Package pw.ollie.politics.world.plot

Class Plot

  • java.lang.Object
    • pw.ollie.politics.world.plot.Plot
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Storable
    public final class Plot
extends Object
implements Storable
    A plot in Politics is made up of exactly one chunk, and may have sub-plots.

      • getSubplot

        public Subplot getSubplot​(int id)
        Gets the Subplot within this Plot with the given id.

        Note that Subplot ids are unique within a Plot but multiple Subplots in different Plots may have the same id. If there is no Subplot with the given id inside this Plot, null is returned.

        Parameters:
        id - the id of the Subplot to get
        Returns:
        the Subplot with the given id, or null if there isn't one with that id

      • createSubplot

        public Subplot createSubplot​(Cuboid region,
                             UUID ownerId)
        Attempts to create a new Subplot for this Plot.

        If the created Subplot is invalid or cannot be added to this Plot, returns null. If the Subplot is valid this method will call SubplotCreateEvent when the Subplot is added to the Plot.

        Parameters:
        region - the physical area of the Subplot to create
        ownerId - the unique id of the owner for the new Subplot
        Returns:
        the created Subplot, or null if it was not successfully added to the Plot

      • addSubplot

        public boolean addSubplot​(Subplot subplot)
        Attempts to add the given Subplot to this Plot.

        This method calls SubplotCreateEvent, and will fail if this event is cancelled.

        Parameters:
        subplot - the Subplot to attempt to add to the Plot
        Returns:
        whether the Subplot was successfully added

      • removeSubplot

        public boolean removeSubplot​(Subplot subplot)
        Attempts to remove the given Subplot from this Plot.

        This method calls SubplotDestroyEvent, and will fail if this event is cancelled.

        Parameters:
        subplot - the Subplot to attempt to remove from the Plot
        Returns:
        whether the Subplot was successfully removed

        public List<Group> getOwners()

        Returns:

      • setOwner

        public boolean setOwner​(int id)
        Attempts to set the direct owner Group of this Plot to the Group with the given unique id.

        This method calls PlotOwnerChangeEvent and will fail if this event is cancelled. It will also fail if no Group with the given unique id exists.

        Parameters:
        id - the unique id of the Group to designate as this Plot's new owner
        Returns:
        whether the owner of the Plot was successfully changed

      • setOwner

        public boolean setOwner​(Group group)
        Attempts to set the direct owner Group of this Plot to the given Group.

        This method calls PlotOwnerChangeEvent and will fail if this event is cancelled.

        Parameters:
        group - the Group to designate as this Plot's new owner
        Returns:
        whether the owner of the Plot was successfully changed

      • removeOwner

        public boolean removeOwner()
        Attempts to remove the direct owner Group of this Plot. This will also remove all Subplots from this Plot without calling events for their removal.

        This method calls PlotOwnerChangeEvent and will fail if this event is cancelled.

        Returns:
        whether the owner of the Plot was successfully changed
